From: Mono OpenWrt Integration <integration@mono.local>
Date: Thu, 3 Jul 2026 12:30:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: swphy: add 10G fixed-link speed mapping

fixed_phy registration on the Mono Gateway DK SFP+ ports fails for a 10G
fixed-link because swphy_decode_speed() has no case for speed 10000; it
falls through to the "unsupported" default and fixed_phy_add() rejects
the link. Map 10000 onto the same SWMII_SPEED_1000 regs entry used for
1000, since swphy has no native 10G register encoding.

Side effect: the emulated BMSR this produces makes ethtool report the
link as 1000 Mb/s even though the datapath actually runs at 10G. This is
cosmetic only; actual throughput and negotiation are unaffected.

---
--- a/drivers/net/phy/swphy.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/swphy.c
@@ -71,6 +71,7 @@ static const struct swmii_regs duplex[] = {
 static int swphy_decode_speed(int speed)
 {
 	switch (speed) {
+	case 10000:
 	case 1000:
 		return SWMII_SPEED_1000;
 	case 100:
